comments: Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Green's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Green (HOU) reaches in and initiates contact to Booker (PHX) that does not affect his SQBR during the drive to the basket.
Sengun (HOU) maintains legal guarding position defending Booker's (PHX) driving shot attempt and dislodges the ball before incidental arm contact occurs.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Green's (HOU) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Sengun (HOU) makes contact with Booker's (PHX) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) and Green (HOU) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Bridges (PHX) immediately slides his hand off of Sengun's (HOU) arm and marginal contact occurs during the pick.

Replay review of the foul called on Bridges (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Bridges (PHX) jumps towards Porter Jr. (HOU) during his shooting motion and initiates contact to his body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Green (HOU) and Booker (PHX) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Green's (HOU) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Booker (PHX) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Green (HOU) during the jump shot attempt.
Bridges (PHX) defends Porter Jr. (HOU) and momentarily places his hands against his body before correcting.
Ayton (PHX) brings his arm toward Green's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs during Green's (HOU) drive.
Ayton (PHX) jumps somewhat towards Green (HOU) after his gather and cleanly dislodges his driving shot attempt before incidental contact occurs.
Booker (PHX) briefly grasps and then quickly releases Gordon's (HOU) jersey as the screen is set.
Booker (PHX) engages with Smith Jr. (HOU) and marginal body contact occurs as he gathers the inbound pass.
Booker (PHX) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Smith Jr.'s (HOU) arm.
Ayton (PHX) jumps somewhat toward Sengun (HOU) and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Green's (HOU) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Porter Jr. (HOU) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before releasing his pass.
Sengun (HOU) brings his hands toward Booker (PHX) and marginal contact occurs as Sengun (HOU) releases away to roll.
Bridges (PHX) briefly places his hand to Green's (HOU) front and marginal contact occurs as he slides his arm off defending his drive to the basket.
Sengun (HOU) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Bridges (PHX) initiates contact with Green's (HOU) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) and Fernando (HOU) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Ayton (PHX) clamps and holds Fernando's (HOU) arm, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Green (HOU) brings his arm toward Booker's (PHX) path and marginal contact occurs during Booker's (PHX) drive.
Green (HOU) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Bridges (PHX) and Porter Jr. (HOU) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Smith Jr. (HOU) moves alongside Bridges (PHX) and marginal lower body contact occurs as Bridges's (PHX) slightly extends his leg out during his shot attempt at the basket.
Ayton (PHX) elevates himself to ball height and brushes Fernado's (HOU) arm as they pursue the loose ball.
Porter Jr. (HOU) releases the ball prior to stepping out of bounds.
Bridges (PHX) and Porter Jr. (HOU) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
